Headline: Must-watch videos of the week
Article_Body: A strange image appears in the sky, a billionaire busts a move and a famous power couple gets mocked. Here are the must-see videos of the week. Devil horns or bikini? A mysterious image taken over the Persian Gulf set the internet on fire with wild speculation. Are you wondering what it really is? Watch to find out. Elon cuts a rug Billionaire Elon Musk boogied on stage at a Tesla event in Shanghai, demonstrating that his moves aren't as smooth as riding in one of his company's cars. It just goes to show that all the money in the world can't buy rhythm. Musk called his dancing "not safe for work." Double vision A Florida mom was seeing quadruple after giving birth to two sets of twins in the same year. She called it a blessing after both of her grandmothers lost twins at birth. Royally roasted Prince Harry and Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, got the late-night treatment after they announced they are stepping back from their roles as senior members of the British royal family. Trevor Noah pitched an interesting new career for Harry if they move to the US. TV personality sparks backlash Lizzo's fans weren't feeling "good as hell" after trainer Jillian Michaels questioned why the singer is being celebrated for her body instead of her music. Lizzo has not publicly responded, but the comments come days after Lizzo announced she is leaving Twitter because of bullies.
